arch:property.oc:show_val: Tiny unit consisting mostly of fragments in the 1-3 cm range. Fragments are mostly slightly weathered, but there is some moderate weathering. Surfaces look worn. Carbonized pieces comprise 10 % of the unit. Mostly sheep-size, a couple of cattle-size. Looks like empty fill or construction material. Certainly not like midden as described on the unit sheet. Sample 2 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. A rather large sample, largely composed of tiny rolled fragments, many of them digested. Heavily weighted toward sheep-size animals, with a bit of smaller mammal, a little large mammal, and some bird. Quite fragmented, but a few pieces up to 4-5 cm. Although in quantity it approaches a midden sample, it still looks more like fill. Last record = 139

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
